{
  "stem": "9995.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Did these relatives live near you?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, some.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One uncle actually lived in another city, but it was about half an hour by train.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was called Bochnia.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And everybody else lived in Cracow.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, combination, I guess.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My grandfather-- we were what is here called conservative.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In Polish, it was [POLISH].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But it was, of course, a kosher home.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And as a matter of fact, my great-- great, great grandfather founded a synagogue, which was also in Cracow, and was, of course, destroyed during the war.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He lived to be 113, so he felt he owed something to his spiritual part.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But in school, especially in my gymnasium, I was only with gentile people, with Catholics.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I grew among them, so I knew both.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But of course, I felt my Jewishness because although there was very little, really, anti-Semitic feelings towards me, there was one girl in our class whose father and mother were both university professors, and she was fiercely anti-Jewish.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And once I was almost thrown out of school because she told me, Jew, go to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I slapped her face, which was an unusual thing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But it was-- I couldn't take it because I was never confronted with much anti-Semitic feelings, although I knew they existed.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And as a matter of fact, the police in our school saved me, and he said, she should not be thrown out from school because it was just a reaction to what she considered an insult.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So I stayed.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, this was the best school in the city.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It-- schools which were governmental schools, unlike here, with the exception of a few schools, like Bronx High School of Science and whatever, this was the best school and was very hard, especially for Jewish child, to get there.",
      "word_count": 39
    }
  ],
